    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've created:\n\n## Plan: `Bun.INI` Public API\n\n### What I explored\n- Read all 4 existing format objects: `TOMLObject.zig`, `JSONCObject.zig`, `JSON5Object.zig` (the closest model since it has both `parse` and `stringify`)\n- Read the full wiring chain: `BunObject.zig` (lazy property registration + getter functions + imports), `BunObject+exports.h` (C++ macro declarations), and `BunObject.cpp` (hash table entries)\n- Read `bun-types/bun.d.ts` for the TypeScript namespace patterns\n- Read the existing INI test to understand the format\n\n### What the plan covers\n\n**1 new file, 5 edits:**\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig` (**new**) | Self-contained `create`, `parse`, `stringify` |\n| `src/bun.js/api.zig` | Add `pub const INIObject = @import(...)` |\n| `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig` | Add lazy prop `INI`, getter `getINIObject`, import `INIObject` |\n| `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h` | Add `macro(INI)` between `Glob` and `JSON5` |\n| `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp` | Add `INI BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI` to hash table |\n| `packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts` | Add `namespace INI` with JSDoc |\n\n**`INIObject.zig` implementation:**\n- `parse`: line-by-line, `[section]`→nested objects, `key=value` pairs, `;`/`#` comments, `SyntaxError` with line number on bad input\n- `stringify`: two-pass (flat values first, then `[section]` blocks), uses `wtf.StringBuilder`\n- Uses `bun.String.borrowUTF8` + `putMayBeIndex` for dynamic keys (same as `JSON5Object.zig`)",
